{"id": "d9s70b", "title": "Thoughts on Skating Condor", "selftext": "Some call it the double diagonal i.e.  [https://www.optionsplaybook.com/option-strategies/double-diagonal-spread/](https://www.optionsplaybook.com/option-strategies/double-diagonal-spread/) \n\nI'm calling it skating condor because I want to roll the short strangle weekly instead of monthly.\n\nLet's take everyone's favorite AAPL - current price $220; earnings set for Nov 7\n\nLong Nov 8 200 Put (Cost 2.30)\n\nShort Oct 4 215 Call (Credit 1.25)\n\nShort Oct 4 225 Call ( Credit .94)\n\nLong Nov 8 240 Call (Cost 2.10)\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nThen you roll the weekly short strangle...  should be able to do it about 4 times.  Theta decay is greatest in the week of expiration and what I've been doing is legging in and out of the weeklies as price fluctuates.\n\n&amp;#x200B;\n\nThoughts?", "created_utc": 1569541852, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/d9s70b/thoughts_on_skating_condor/", "is_self": true}